stylometry: Again, this tradeoff when deciding how much inventory to order is that having too much inventory can make a business lose money, and not having enough inventory for customers to purchase you will lose money also - therefore a company must balance the inventory amount to have enough for demand but also to not run out. EOQ = economic order quantity; it is the equation for inventory that gives a company the optimized order quantity it must hold in order to avoid the risk of stock out between when an order is placed and received. Clearly, EOQ equalizing the inventory factor of stock out; it will help the company to balance inventory to meet their demand and still have inventory left over for either a next order, or for back up stock.
